00:25:18.380 --> 00:25:22.200
And we're not that
old yet, so it's hard.

00:25:22.200 --> 00:25:23.621
So here's a nudge.

00:25:23.621 --> 00:25:25.370
If you open up your
refrigerator-- picture

00:25:25.370 --> 00:25:27.140
this in your mind-- what's
sitting on the middle shelf

00:25:27.140 --> 00:25:28.973
there, that big shelf
right in front of you?

00:25:28.973 --> 00:25:29.830
What's in there?

00:25:29.830 --> 00:25:31.770
I see people
laughing and smiling.

00:25:31.770 --> 00:25:33.340
You going to admit it?

00:25:33.340 --> 00:25:35.160
No.

00:25:35.160 --> 00:25:36.540
Usually, you got,
like, you might

00:25:36.540 --> 00:25:38.880
have some juice, some
milk, maybe some take-out

00:25:38.880 --> 00:25:42.230
containers, some leftovers
from the restaurant last night.

00:25:42.230 --> 00:25:44.767
Everything that is high in
calories, low in nutritional

00:25:44.767 --> 00:25:46.850
content right there, because
that's the big space.

00:25:46.850 --> 00:25:49.220
That's where all those
big things go, right?

00:25:49.220 --> 00:25:51.500
Where are your vegetables?

00:25:51.500 --> 00:25:57.200
